+
+---
+
+## Risks & Mitigations
+
+- **Vite 8 + Node 20 minimum:** Vite 8 requires Node 20.19+ / 22.12+. The project pins
+  Node 20+; ensure CI and local use ≥ 20.19 (use a `.nvmrc` with `20.19.0` or `22`). If
+  pinning to an older Node 20 patch is required, fall back to **Vite ^7.x** (also supported
+  by Vitest 4.1.9 per its peer range `^6.0.0 || ^7.0.0 || ^8.0.0`). **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Canvas 2D not implemented in happy-dom/jsdom:** Unit tests that exercise rendering must
+  mock `CanvasRenderingContext2D` methods (`fillRect`, `clearRect`, …) with `vi.fn()`
+  spies. Pure game-logic tests (move/push/win/undo/storage/glob-load) need no canvas mock.
+  **Confidence: HIGH** on the requirement; **MEDIUM** on the exact mock surface (finalize
+  during implementation by listing the `ctx` methods actually called).
+- **GitHub Pages base path:** If the repo is not `<user>.github.io` root, `vite.config.ts`
+  must set `base: '/<repo>/'` (or `base: './'` for relative assets). The eager-glob choice
+  makes level loading immune to this (JSON is inlined), but any `fetch`/asset URL must
+  respect `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`. Recommendation A avoids this entirely. **Confidence:
+  HIGH.**
+- **Pointer Events on older iOS Safari:** Pointer Events are supported in Safari ≥ 13
+  (2019). Set `touch-action: none` on the canvas to prevent page-scroll interference.
+  **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **`localStorage` in private mode:** Safari throws on `setItem` in private mode; the
+  `storage.ts` wrapper must `try/catch` both read and write and degrade gracefully
+  (in-memory only). **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Eager glob picks up stray JSON:** `import.meta.glob('./levels/*.json', …)` will include
+  any `.json` added under `levels/`. Use a strict glob like `./levels/level-??.json` or
+  validate filenames in the parser to avoid accidentally shipping a `levels/test.json`.
+  **Confidence: HIGH.**
+- **Tween interruption correctness:** When a new move cancels an in-flight tween, the
+  "from" position of the new tween must be the **current interpolated** position, not the
+  last discrete tile — otherwise the sprite snaps. This is a one-line detail but easy to
+  get wrong; cover with a Vitest test. **Confidence: HIGH.**
+
+---
+
+## Out of Scope (intentionally not adopted)
+
+- **React / Solid / Vue** — Canvas 2D rendering is imperative; a UI framework would add
+  40–100 KB and a DOM-diffing model that does not match the render loop. Rejected.
+- **anime.js / motion** — solving a linear lerp with a 16–50 KB library violates
+  simplicity-first. Rejected (kept as LOW-confidence contingency only).
+- **Hammer.js** — unmaintained since 2016, superseded by Pointer Events. Rejected.
+- **idb-keyval / localforage** — IndexedDB wrappers for a < 1 KB sync-read persistence
+  need. Rejected.
+- **Fixed-timestep game loop** — designed for continuous physics, not discrete puzzle
+  moves with short linear tweens. Rejected.
+- **Zod / runtime schema validation for levels** — 10 hand-authored JSON files with a
+  documented schema; a hand-written `parseLevel(raw): Level | throws` validator is
+  sufficient and dependency-free. Rejected (note: if level count grows or levels become
+  community-supplied, revisit). **Confidence: MEDIUM.**
+
+---
+
+*Versions verified against the npm registry on 2026-07-01. Confidence labels reflect
+direct verification (HIGH), established-but-unverified-in-session patterns (MEDIUM), or
+speculative/contingency picks (LOW).*
