+# Research Summary: sokoban
+
+> Synthesis of `bp/research/stack.md`, `bp/research/architecture.md`, and `bp/research/pitfalls.md`. Single recommendation that all three sub-agents converged on; deviations from the locked grill-phase decisions are zero.
+
+---
+
+## One-Line Recommendation
+
+A **layered TypeScript architecture** — pure functional reducer for game rules + thin imperative shell for Canvas / input / animation / persistence — built with **Vite 8 + vanilla helpers** (no state lib, no animation lib, no swipe lib, no storage wrapper), loaded with **`import.meta.glob` eager JSON**, animated by a **30-line rAF linear tween**, persisted with **raw `localStorage` + try/catch**, and tested with **Vitest + happy-dom** (logic) and **Playwright on `vite preview`** (E2E, desktop + mobile).
+
+---
+
+## Convergence Matrix
+
+| Direction | Stack says | Architecture says | Pitfalls says | Verdict |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Level loading | `import.meta.glob` (Vite native) | `import.meta.glob` (eager) | **BLOCKER #12** if you use `fetch` under sub-path → adopt glob | **Glob** |
+| State management | Plain `GameModel` + 20-line emitter | Pure reducer + thin shell | Anti-pattern: don't add React/Solid for a single Canvas game | **Reducer + shell** |
+| Animation | Vanilla rAF linear tween (~30 lines) | Snap-then-start tween, rAF loop, no fixed timestep | **BLOCKER #4, #5** if state mutates inside rAF or inputs queue | **rAF + wall-clock lerp** |
+| Touch input | Native Pointer Events + `touch-action: none` | Pointer Events + 24px threshold | **BLOCKER #9** if swipe is attached to `document` / no `touch-action` | **Pointer Events scoped to canvas** |
+| localStorage | Vanilla + try/catch, sync read on boot | Single `storage.ts` owner, namespaced + versioned | **BLOCKER #6, MAJOR #7, #8** for throws / null / schema migration | **Vanilla localStorage** |
+| Game loop | Single rAF, idle-stop, frame-rate independent via `performance.now()` | Wall-clock lerp (not fixed timestep) | — | **rAF + idle-stop** |
+| Unit test env | `happy-dom` (faster than jsdom); mock `CanvasRenderingContext2D` | Core tests are pure TS — no DOM needed for logic tests | — | **happy-dom, scoped via `environmentMatchGlobs`** |
+| E2E target | `vite preview` against `dist/` + desktop + mobile projects | — | **MAJOR #19** if E2E only runs against dev server | **`vite preview` + Playwright projects** |
+
+All three sub-agents converged on the same stack and architecture with zero conflict. The BLOCKERs flagged in pitfalls are all addressed by the recommended architecture decisions.
+
+---
+
