+| Commit linter | `@commitlint/cli` + `@commitlint/config-conventional` + `husky` | ^19.x / v9 | Conventional Commits enforcement | HIGH |
+| Deploy | `actions/deploy-pages@v4` | GitHub-provided | Static `dist/` to Pages | HIGH |
+
+**Rejected (with reason):** React/Solid (imperative Canvas, 40–100 KB), motion / anime.js (16–50 KB to do `lerp`), Hammer.js (unmaintained since 2016), idb-keyval / localforage (< 1 KB sync data), Zod (10 hand-authored files), fixed-timestep loop (no continuous physics).
+
+---
+
+## Recommended Architecture
+
+- **`core/`** — pure functions: `reducer(state, intent) → { state, anim? }`, `winCheck`, `move`, `history`. Zero DOM/Canvas imports. Fully unit-testable.
+- **`shell/gameShell.ts`** — only module that knows all subsystems; owns rAF loop; forwards intents → reducer → animator → renderer.
+- **`render/`** — pure draw: `(state, visualPos, ctx) → pixels`. Redraws full canvas every frame (≤30 entities, trivial).
+- **`input/`** — produces `Intent`. Keyboard (`keydown`, `repeat` guard) + Pointer Events swipe. Buttons go through the same `dispatch`.
+- **`anim/`** — vanilla rAF tween manager: `start / isBusy / elapsed / snap`. Snap-then-start for interruption.
+- **`storage/`** — single owner of `localStorage`. Versioned keys (`sokoban:v1:*`). Try/catch → graceful degradation.
+- **`ui/`** — DOM overlays (level picker, HUD, win banner, mobile buttons). CSS handles responsive layout.
+- **`level/`** — `loader.ts` uses `import.meta.glob`; `validate.ts` enforces schema + invariants (`boxes.length === targets.size`, all positions in bounds, no entity on wall).
+
+### State model (immutable)
+
+```ts
+type GameState = {
+  levelId: string;
+  static: { width, height, walls: Set<Coord>, targets: Set<Coord> };
+  player: Coord;
+  boxes: Coord[];              // order-stable, index = box identity
+  moveCount: number;
+  history: HistoryEntry[];     // entry-based undo stack
+  won: boolean;                // recomputed by winCheck
+};
+
+type HistoryEntry = {
+  player: Coord;               // before move
+  pushedBoxIndex?: number;
+  boxFrom?: Coord;
+  moveCount: number;
+};
+```
+
+### Data flow
+
+`raw event → InputPipeline.normalize → Intent → GameShell.dispatch → gameReducer → { state, anim? } → Animator.start → rAF → Renderer.draw → Canvas`
+
+### Critical algorithms
+
+- **Win check:** `O(B)` — `boxes.every(b => targets.has(b))` after `boxes.length === targets.size` precheck. Recomputed on move, undo, reset.
+- **Undo:** entry-based O(1) per move, unlimited depth (NFR-6). Walk entries store only `player` + `moveCount`; push entries add `pushedBoxIndex` + `boxFrom`.
+- **Animation interrupt:** snap current tween → commit visual → start fresh tween from current visual. No input queueing.
+
+---
+
+## Top Risks (BLOCKERs) and How the Recommendation Mitigates Them
+
+| BLOCKER | Mitigation via the recommended approach |
+|---|---|
+| #3 Undo correctness | `HistoryEntry` snapshots player AND pushed box before applying move; reducer overwrites state wholesale on undo. Vitest cases for push/walk/empty-stack/reset-undo. |
+| #4 Undo mid-animation | Logical state commits synchronously at input; tween is render-only interpolation. Undo pops stack + restarts tween from current visual. rAF never mutates logical state. |
+| #5 Animation interrupt | Snap-then-start: cancel in-flight tween, commit visual, start new from snapped position. Single `currentTween` handle. |
+| #6 localStorage throws (Safari private / quota) | `storage.ts` wraps every read/write in try/catch; on failure → in-memory fallback, one-time toast, game still playable. |
+| #9 Touch swipe scrolls the page | Pointer Events scoped to canvas + `touch-action: none` + `event.preventDefault()` on `touchmove`. Directional threshold (~24px). |
+| #11 GitHub Pages base path | `base: '/<repo>/'` env-driven in `vite.config.ts`; eager `import.meta.glob` inlines levels (immune to base path). E2E runs against `vite preview` of `dist/` to verify. |
+| #12 JSON level path under sub-path | Eager `import.meta.glob('./levels/level-??.json', { eager: true, query: '?json', import: 'default' })` — JSON inlined into bundle, no runtime fetch, no path issues. |
+
+Plus **11 MAJOR** risks (deadlock detection, reset/undo interaction, DPR scaling, key-repeat guard, persistence correctness, E2E-vs-build mismatch, CI gating) — all mitigated by concrete code patterns and test coverage documented in `pitfalls.md`.
+
+---
+
+## Critical Implementation Details (must not skip)
+
+1. **`vite.config.ts` base path:** `base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/sokoban/'` (or `'./'` for user pages).
+2. **Canvas DPR:** `canvas.width = cssW * dpr; canvas.height = cssH * dpr; ctx.setTransform(dpr, 0, 0, dpr, 0, 0)` — and re-apply on resize.
+3. **CSS:** `touch-action: none` on the canvas element.
+4. **Keyboard:** `if (event.repeat) return;` to enforce one-tile-per-press (FR-1).
+5. **Undo correctness:** always recompute `won = winCheck(state)` on undo AND reset, not only on move.
+6. **localStorage namespace:** `sokoban:v1:cleared`, `sokoban:v1:best:<id>`. Versioned for future migration.
+7. **`import.meta.glob` filename pattern:** strict glob `./levels/level-??.json` to avoid picking up stray files.
+8. **Snap-then-start animation:** `animator.snap()` finalizes tween before next reducer call.
+9. **Reset semantics:** clear undo stack on reset (reset = fresh start boundary). Document and test.
+10. **Commit enforcement:** husky v9 + commitlint — `.husky/commit-msg` shell file; v8→v9 changed format.
+11. **CI workflow:** `npm ci → npm test → npm run test:e2e → npm run build → upload dist/`; deploy job `needs: test`.
+12. **E2E server:** Playwright `webServer: { command: 'npm run preview', port: 4173 }` to test the real built artifact, not dev.
+
+---
+
